-- Einhorn's hedge fund adds new positions in Micron and BP -letter
-- By Svea Herbst-Bayliss
-- Wed Jan 22, 2014 11:58AM EST
-- None



BOSTON, Jan 22 (Reuters) - Hedge fund manager David Einhorn, whose Greenlight Capital ranked among last year's best performers, said he had taken new stakes in BP Plc <BP.L>, Anadarko Petroleum Corp <APC.N> and Micron Technology Inc <MU.O>.

The fund returned 19.5 percent last year. Einhorn said bets on iPad and iPhone maker Apple Inc <AAPL.O>, General Motors Co <GM.N>, the Japanese yen and Micron had boosted returns, while Chipotle Mexican Grill Inc <CMG.N> and U.S. Steel Corp <X.N> hurt.